\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid7014491 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 What year were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14104528 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 1917. On the third of November.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 What year were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 1895.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
In Paddington Green police station. And - my father he - used to have F.R. on his epaulette because he was called for special duty, you know, and he used to get thirty shillings a week for that and that's what my mo
ther had to keep us all on until we grew - grew up - yes - until we grew up. And - they used to carry truncheon, whistle, gloves and a note book. And hanging from his belt was a piece of leather which held their lamp and they used to have an oil lamp, you
 
know, they used to have a man come and fill these lamps every week, you know, or each day I believe it was now they used to have to clean them out and do - but - then they had a cape - a big cape for the wintertime - it was a huge great thing and they use
d
 to have to fold it up in such a special way and used to see them leave it in the doorways of shops and different things, you know, have it in a special place every time on their beat. And - they had a certain way of rolling it up and there was everything
 
convenience like opposite the police station we had a bakers and - then there was - you know, a laundry and all sorts - everything that you could think of. Sweet shop and - there was a coffee shop I believe what the men used to go into sometimes. And - Mr
s
 Severn, you know Mrs Severn in Paddington did you? Haven't you seen the statue of Mrs Seddon and the Seddon school - they've got a school at Paddington now called the - Sarah Seddon school - yes. Well she was buried at the back of - Paddington Green real
l
y. She was sort of - mausoleum I think or something like that. And I know we used to go to school through this - churchyard and we used to be so, you know, sedate and wonder how we're going to tread across the ground, you know, because it was consecrated.
 And - then we had Pickfords at the side of us where the horses used to go up to bed of a night, you know, they'd go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1317777\charrsid9327351 blop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
, blop, blop up to bed. Up the slope, they had a slope there and of course it was all horse - horses then in those days. And the local b
read that used to be tuppence ha'penny and sugar, penny farthing. We used to get that up the Home and Colonial in Edgware Road. My mother used to go up there - once a week, you know, to get all the grocery. And - Father Christmas of course he was at Gardn
ers and we used to go and see him every Christmas, you know, used to tap on his window and he'd come with a present to give us. And - the film The Blue Lamp that was taken from Paddington Green Police station. You remember The Blue Lamp - the film.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 It isn't the Paddington Green that Jack Warner ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, yes, yes, yes. Yes, that's Paddington Green police station. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 How many years did you live in the house you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Well I moved when I was seven. I came to Queens Park and I've been on here ever since I was seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 On this estate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes. I was at thirty-nine Fifth Avenue. And from there I went to Second Avenue with my mother and father. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Your father left the police station when he left the police did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Do you know why you moved houses on this estate?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1317777\charrsid9327351 Well, we lived with Council}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5602767\charrsid9327351 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1317777\charrsid9327351 or Waycock in Fifth Avenue and he was a marble mason and traveled the world, you know, collecting marbles and he used to have the Primrose League, you know,
 meetings and my mother used to keep the two rooms that he had clean and we had the rest of the house because they were big houses down Fifth Avenue, you know, the first class houses. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
And - from there we went to Second Avenue. And - lived with my mother - my mother and father died from there and of course we all got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14104528 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
 and - went from home. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 I had four sisters and two brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Whereabouts in the family did you come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 I was the last 
but one. I was last but one. And - the buses were all open decked you know and they used to have mackintosh covers across and in the wet weather, you know, used to get - they used to cross the knees and used to run down and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 But your head was still getting wet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
Yes. But we didn't - we really loved it you know to get up onto the bus. And there was horse drawn trams along Harrow Road and they used to have a horse go at the bottom of the bridge and bring the tram up, you know, into the - up the hil
l. And of course that was all done away with and then they went and extended it to Edgware Road, you know, put them right through to Edgware Road. And - the band used to play on the lawn at Paddington station every Saturday. I don't know whether it does n
o
w but it used to do that. And most of the lamps were gas, do you remember that, gas lamps - yes, they were all gas. And they used to have a man come round, you know, and poke a stick up and light the light. And even round in Queens Park, even on a foggy n
i
ght - because we had a lamp outside our house one time - it was an ordinary lamp - he used to poke the stick up through and light it and - but it wouldn't matter if it was ten or one in the morning, you know, you could hear him come up these stairs and li
ght the light. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Have you any idea how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Oh, now - how old was he now - no, I really can't think of that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Do you know where he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, they both came from Norfolk both of them. Yes, 
both from Norfolk. My mother come from Snettisham and my father came from Docking - Docking - Docking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 What did he do when he left the police force?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Well he had a - a place on the Borough Council. They gave him a job on the Borough Council. And 
- oh and when they used to tar these pavements on Queens Park they used to get down on their hands and knees to do it and they used to be the - Italian people that used to do it - and they used to do it on their hands and knees - it was marvel}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322054\charrsid9327351 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 ous the way 
they did it, you know, all so smooth and nice you know. So different - ally by hand - used to get down on their hands and knees with a - a wooden block and go all over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 The Italians used to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, Recu - Regushia was their name - Regushi
a. And it was very strange because the - my - old house in thirty-nine, Fifth Avenue is a - a lady down in there who my husband used to go to school with her husband and - you know, she can remember all about Droop Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Very much a village community this is isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
Yes. It - well it was in - in olden days, you know, there were more neighbourly than what they are really. Well my - my husband was the top boy at Droop Street school, yes, and he was for many years. I've given my grandson all his
 medals, he never stopped away from school one day, now that's a record isn't it? No, he's got all those medals and now - Philip's got them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 He got them for attendance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, punctuality and attendance, you know, used to be all colours, you know
, gold silver and bronze, you know, the little bar on it was bronze and all sorts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Do you remember your father ever being out of work in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 He always had a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes. Always had a job - yes. Oh he was a - real o
ne and so was my own husband, I mean he worked very hard - he was fifty-eight years on the West - Great Western and I don't think that - barring for losing his fingers and being away he was ever away from work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Do you know if your mother ever worked before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14104528 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 She didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 It was unusual in those days wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 She didn't work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14104528 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No. No, no, no. She had enough to do with six children. But she really did work hard, you 
know, I mean to say - used to make all their clothing and - you know, do everything that she could in the way of - in the house. And there used to be a funny old lady used to live up on the top floor and all the children used to run to carry her basket an
d
 my mother used to say to me, now you're not to take anything from - you do that for a la - you know, a labour of love, you know, and we used to carry this basket right up over the top and when we got up the top there she'd give us a farthing. That was ou
r labour of love - so we didn't get paid for the rest of the day. Yes. Oh my word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 In which house did you live the longest when you were a child - in Fifth Avenue?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No - well, I lived in nine, Sixth Avenue when I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14104528 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351  and then from there we went up to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 But when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Oh, Fifth Avenue - I moved to Fifth Avenue when I was seven years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 How many rooms were there in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 There was one, two - four upstairs I think - yes, yes. There'd be four down I think then. Yes, four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 The kitchen and the scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, four down. 'Course they had a bathroom there - little bathroom at the back in those days, you know. Yes, they had a little bathroom.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 They were superior things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes. Oh they were f
irst class house you see and they had one of the biggest gardens on Queens Park - longest gardens, yes. We used to have a - a little glass house and we had a swing in there, I can always remember it, you know, and swinging out through to this glasshouse.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did anyone else live with you - any relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did your mother have anyone to help her in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No, no, used to do it all her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did your mother or father mend or make the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
Yes, my father used to have to do all the boots and shoes and look after them and clean them. He used to line them up you know, all of them clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did your mother make any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, she used to make all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1317777\charrsid9327351 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351  clothes - yes. Coats and perhaps somebody'd have a dress that could be cut down and that used to do for somebody else and - it was marvellous really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 And you couldn't run up a dress in a day in those days could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
Oh no, and you - you didn't get them, you know, straight out of the shops and that sort of thing. They had to sit down and make do and mend, you know, and so they - they was very industrious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Your clothes were always new - you never had to have secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No, no, used to have them you know, made - they was always new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 You never bought any hardly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 But you bought shoes - you didn't have these made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No, we had to have - we - they bought shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 They bought them ready made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, yes, yes. But my father always used to see to them, you know, see that they was in good repair and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did your father help your mother with any jobs in the house like cleaning, cooking, washing up, the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No, he wasn't so - you know - like my own husband, you know, he was very domesticated but I don't think my father was that way inclined.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did he do any decorating or repairs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 No, no, he never did any of that - no. But my own hus
band he wasn't very good at decorating but he would cook a dinner as good as I could cook it, you know. Marvellous he was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Do you remember your father ever dressing or undressing or bathing you - reading to you or telling you stories or anything like that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
Well, he'd always do it if - you know, was needs be, but he wasn't one that would - you know, would do - regular thing, no. Had to do it or if mother was ill or anything like that he'd put his hand to the wheel.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did you ever go out with your father without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
Oh yes, we used to go out Sunday mornings. He used to take us up - used to be Kensington Gardens then, you know, through Sussex Gardens into Kensington Gardens and we used to go around the statues and fountains - 
I don't know whether you know it at all - Peter Pan, you know, little Peter Pan. He used to take us there - we used to stand for hours watching Peter Pan. And along the Serpentine, you know, in the boats. It was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did your father look after you if your mother had to go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Well, I - she very seldom ever went out. No, she had too much to do - too much to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Oh yes, indeed yes. We had the - always on a Saturday mornin
g we had to do the silver and - you know, whatever little jobs there were to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 And your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes. They all helped - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 What kind of things would they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Dust and all sorts of things we had to, you know, make
 ourselves busy. We never and same by doing little sewing jobs and that you know. Used to have to mend different things - we didn't have to go out to play then, we had to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 After you left school did you have to do things at home as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes
, yes, we - I used to - well, I used to go to tennis after - when I - school you know. I used to go up to - Paddington Recreation ground and I mean they would never think of doing a thing like that today would they - walk all the way up to Paddington - th
at's after school we used to go up there and play tennis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did the older children help the younger ones with things they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Oh yes, my eldest brother, he was really most helpful. You know, he'd do anything for me - he'd run and get m
y milk anyway. And he used to be - you know - put me through it too - used to put me up on top of a cupboard and leave me there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Do you remember them helping you with dressing or eating when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Oh yes, yes. Yes, we would really help one another. We were very united family - very united.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 And the younger ones would help the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, had to be to bed sharp at eight o'clock in the school time - always had to be in bed by eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
Well sometimes we went on our own and then we used to get up to pranks at times and father'd come and promise us but we'd be playing obstacle races -
 over the bed with a pillow and one thing and another, you know. We made our own enjoyment - we did enjoy ourselves more so than they do today, you know, we always found something to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 How old were you when you started to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Well, about - seven or eight - we used to go to bed on our own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did you share the bedroom with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 My youngest sister - this was the one I was always brought up with, you know, the youngest one - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 And the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 My two brothers - you see, my two brothers and - of course they were growing up you see when we were - young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 They'd have another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, they had a - the two boys were downstairs as a matter of fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 So you had enough room just to have two in each room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 That was unusual in those days wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Houses were smaller on the whole weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 What room did you bath in - you had a bathroom you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Well, there was a ba
throom in - Fifth Avenue but of course we never had a bathroom in the police station - used to have a hip bath in front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 How often did you have a bath - did you have a ritual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Oh yes, once a week - yes, but we - we, you see, you had 
to be careful because you couldn't be when anybody was about you know, you had to - either they'd gone to bed or something had happened you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Was there a ritual like bath and clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes. Always kept very clean indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 You had your clean clothes after the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
Yes. And of course - we used to always put them out and when my mother - you know when we come in from Sunday school we was always sent to Sunday school every Sunday - we used to go three times as a matter of fact, I 
used to go Sunday mornings, Sunday afternoons and Sunday evenings to church - and when we come home from church we was got our hangers and pegs and covers in those days, used to have to cover our clothes all over and keep them clean and keep the dust from
 
them. But mum was very strict on all that you know and we had to brush our own clothes down and keep them clean. Yes, I don't think they stop to do that these days - they just throw them down don't they. But I mean my grandchildren, they come in they thro
w their clothes down, they never think to hang them up. If it's mother that has to gang them up but my mother never had to hang mine up - no, or my sister's. Always see to their own clothes.
