\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Oh well, tha
t's going back a bit. Now, we had - used to have cereals and - and you know, toast and marmalade and - those sort of things, we still had those. Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did you have anything different on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Oh there was always the meat and the roast, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1317777\charrsid9327351 Yorkshire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 
 and - of course being my parents was Norfolk it was Norfolk dumplings and of course they did it in a different way because they see that you had your Norfolk dumpling before you had your dinner so you wouldn't want much dinner. Yes, we always had 
the dumpling before with the gravy you know but it really was marvelous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did you eat anything different for breakfast on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1008777 GB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Well I suppose we did really - sausages or something like that, you know, be a bit extra for Sunday morning. I supp
ose there was more time really to have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did your mother or father bake their own bread or make jam?
