the poppies - you know - the poppies and the corn, 'course that all had to be sorted out but still it - well, it looked to me, you know, it was really beautiful to wake up in the morning and see that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Yes. And in Norfolk they got these tea roses, you know,
 and they're all round the doors and - they're cream and white doors and they really looked wonderful, how they - and I can always remember that - holidays, you know. They used to - I suppose it was better for them to go home - although my mother was neve
r well when she went home - was the funny thing about it. She was always - yes, but she was very poorly when she went home you know, she never - seemed to enjoy her holiday like we did. We used to have a good time when we were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7014491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10888220\charrsid9327351 Did they keep any livestock for the family?
