ata that my youngest sister, you know, she went as an Indian and what - I was an English girl in that I remember that - we had to all say our different lines and things. But they was more interested in young people in those - in those days, I thought they
 were anyway. You know, they'd give them something to do which I think they're lacking today - they don't have enough to do - they don't give them enough to do.
